                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.51/107: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cottrell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-16T15:00:00-04:32">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 23—5:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Chamber of Deputies yesterday passed bill in approximate form desired by New
                    York bankers authorizing immediate loan of $19,000,000 also additional
                    $4,000,000 as needed for completion Potosi-Sucre railway. Bill also provides
                    that bonds held by Ulen Contracting Corporation be refunded and consolidated
                    with new loan making total amount $33,000,000. Of this sum $24,000,000 are to be
                    offered to public immediately and additional $9,000,000 within next 2 years.</p>
                <p>Little opposition looked for in the Senate where bill is expected to pass this
                        week.<note n="6" xml:id="d382fn6">The loan law was promulgated by President
                        Saavedra, May 24.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cottrell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
